  <prompt>
    Build and deploy the `LegalWorkspace` solution to the dev environment via the `dataverse-deploy` skill. This deploy verifies that the Wave 4 fork deletion (task 061) + consumer retarget (task 062) did not break LegalWorkspace.

    Pre-deploy: confirm LegalWorkspace `npm run build` is clean (this is the FIRST clean build after the intentional break window between tasks 061 → 062). Confirm `@spaarke/ui-components` resolves to a version containing the canonical wrappers and the Wave 4 SummarizeFiles fix.

    Post-deploy: navigate to a surface in LegalWorkspace that previously used the fork (e.g., the parent component that mounted `SummarizeFiles/SummarizeFilesDialog`). Confirm zero console errors on load. Functional smoke test is task 065.

    Note: this task is `parallel-safe: true` in `parallel-group: J` — runs in parallel with task 063 (SummarizeFilesWizard solution deploy). Different solutions; concurrent platform-level deploys are safe.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Deployment engineer familiar with `dataverse-deploy` skill for LegalWorkspace. Knows the Vite build pipeline + solution-import path + dev environment target. Aware of the Wave 4 fork-deletion → retarget transition.
  </role>

  <goal>
    LegalWorkspace solution deployed to dev with Wave 4 fork cleanup shipped. Build clean (the post-061 intentional break is now closed by 062's retargeting). Lint clean. Solution imported successfully. Smoke loading shows zero console errors. Ready for task 065 (functional smoke).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      The Wave 4 sequence:
      - Task 060: Shared `SummarizeFilesDialog.tsx` migrated to canonical wrapper
      - Task 061: LegalWorkspace `SummarizeFiles/` fork (9 files) DELETED — LegalWorkspace build intentionally broken
      - Task 062: LegalWorkspace consumers retargeted to `@spaarke/ui-components` — LegalWorkspace build repaired
      - Task 064 (THIS): Verify LegalWorkspace builds + deploys clean post-cleanup

      This task is the second LegalWorkspace deploy in the project (task 054 was the first, post Wave 3). The deploy steps mirror task 054 — same skill, same target, same pipeline.

      Per CLAUDE.md §11, use `npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund`.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/ (build root)</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/package.json</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/components/SummarizeFiles/ (DELETED in 061; possibly recreated as 5-line shim in 062 if Approach B)</file>
      <file>.claude/skills/dataverse-deploy/SKILL.md</file>
      <file>projects/email-communication-solution-r3/tasks/054-build-deploy-legalworkspace-wave-3.poml (analogous deploy procedure)</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

