  <steps>
    <step order="1">Pre-deploy: from `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/`:
      <code>
      npm install --legacy-peer-deps --no-audit --no-fund
      npm run build
      npm run lint
      </code>
      If any step fails: this signals task 062 left the build broken. Escalate to task 062 — do NOT attempt deploy.
    </step>
    <step order="2">Verify the SummarizeFiles cleanup landed: grep for `solutions/LegalWorkspace.*SummarizeFiles` in `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/`. Should return zero hits (Approach A from 062) OR only the 5-line shim (Approach B). NO original fork code.</step>
    <step order="3">Verify `@spaarke/ui-components` resolves to a Wave 4 version. Inspect `node_modules/@spaarke/ui-components/dist/` for the migrated SummarizeFilesDialog.</step>
    <step order="4">Invoke `dataverse-deploy` skill: target = dev, solution = LegalWorkspace.</step>
    <step order="5">Monitor deploy. On success: capture timestamp + dev URL. On failure: capture error, escalate per category (build → task 062; auth → re-authenticate).</step>
    <step order="6">Post-deploy: load LegalWorkspace in browser DevTools. Confirm zero console errors on page load. Navigate to the parent surface that previously mounted the fork — confirm it still renders (now using canonical).</step>
    <step order="7">Write deploy summary to `notes/wave-4-deploy-legalworkspace.md`: timestamp, dev URL, console-check result, SummarizeFiles fork-cleanup verification result.</step>
    <step order="8">Update `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: mark task 064 ✅ completed.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `projects/email-communication-solution-r3/current-task.md` per task-execute protocol: status → completed, advance to next pending task (065 if 063 also complete; otherwise wait for 063).</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="bash">Run build + lint locally</tool>
    <tool name="grep">Verify fork-cleanup landed</tool>
    <tool name="dataverse-deploy">Solution deploy to dev</tool>
    <tool name="write">Create `notes/wave-4-deploy-legalworkspace.md` deploy summary</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="notes">projects/email-communication-solution-r3/notes/wave-4-deploy-legalworkspace.md (NEW — deploy summary + fork-cleanup verification)</output>
    <output type="deploy">LegalWorkspace solution deployed to dev (post Wave 4 cleanup)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">LegalWorkspace `npm run build` exits 0 (post Wave 4 cleanup).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">LegalWorkspace `npm run lint` exits 0.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Grep for `solutions/LegalWorkspace.*SummarizeFiles` returns zero fork-code hits (only optional 5-line shim).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`dataverse-deploy` skill reports successful solution import to dev.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">LegalWorkspace surface loads in dev with zero JS console errors.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`notes/wave-4-deploy-legalworkspace.md` exists with timestamp, dev URL, console + fork-cleanup verification.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`TASK-INDEX.md` marks task 064 ✅ completed.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    Parallel-group J: this task and 063 (SummarizeFilesWizard solution deploy) target different Dataverse solutions; concurrent execution is safe.

    The pre-deploy build check (step 1) is the critical gate. If LegalWorkspace builds clean, both 061 (fork delete) and 062 (consumer retarget) successfully closed the intentional break window. If build fails, root-cause to task 062 — typically a missed consumer or a canonical-barrel export gap.

    The post-deploy console check (step 6) is a SMOKE-LEVEL check that the runtime imports resolve. It does NOT verify the SummarizeFiles wizard behavior — that is task 065.

    Escalation policy: if any step fails, fix upstream FIRST (typically task 062, since 060 is shared-lib and shouldn't affect LegalWorkspace build directly). Re-run THIS task after upstream fix.
  </notes>

